AI & LLM Key Terms

# Create API Keys
Start with $5: 
https://platform.openai.com/chat 

# Tokens: 
A token is the smallest text unit that a language model processes
https://platform.openai.com/tokenizer 

# Context Window: Total number of tokens that the LLM can examine at any one point, when trying to generate the next token. 
Can only remember what’s within context
Includes original prompt and its output, etc

Bigger Context Windows (32k–128k+)
Good for: Analyzing entire Books or Contracts, Codebases, etc

Smaller Context Windows (2k–8k)
Building Short transactional apps
Single-shot prompts

LLM Leaderboard Comparison: 
Benchmarks across speed, cost, accuracy, and context size
Context window, cost and speed comparison
https://www.vellum.ai/llm-leaderboard
